formatDescription: These are files created by Visual Basic, a software development tool for Windows. The files hold coordinate positions for each window in the visual programming environment, and are used to reload elements into their previous positions after a close/reopen. Visual Basic software has been replaced with Visual Basic.NET., which doesn’t generate .vbw files.
provenanceCompoundName: National Library of Australia / National Library of Australia
